    {"id": "stock-basics", "level": "入门", "category": "股票", "title": "Stock——Stocks (also capital stock, or sometimes interchangeably, sh…", "summary": "Stocks (also capital stock, or sometimes interchangeably, shares) consist of all the shares by which ownership of a corporation or company is divided. A single share of the stock means fractional ownership of the corporation in proportion to the total number of shares.", "takeaways": ["Stocks (also capital stock, or sometimes interchangeably, shares) consist of all the shares by which ownership of a corporation or company is divided.", "As new shares are issued by a company, the ownership and rights of existing shareholders are diluted in return for cash to sustain or grow the busines…", "Stock bought and sold in private markets fall within the private equity realm of finance."], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stock"},
    {"id": "common-stock", "level": "入门", "category": "股票", "title": "Common stock——Common stock is a form of corporate equity ownership, a type…", "summary": "Common stock is a form of corporate equity ownership, a type of security. The terms voting share and ordinary share are also used frequently outside of the United States. They are known as equity shares or ordinary shares in the UK and other Commonwealth realms.", "takeaways": ["Common stock is a form of corporate equity ownership, a type of security.", "The owners of common stock do not directly own any assets of the company; instead each stockholder owns a fractional interest in the company, which in…", "Over the long term, common stocks tend to outperform more secure investments, despite their short-term volatility."], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_stock"},
    {"id": "preferred-stock", "level": "入门", "category": "股票", "title": "Preferred stock——Preferred stock (also called preferred shares, preference sh…", "summary": "Preferred stock (also called preferred shares, preference shares, or simply preferreds) is a component of share capital that may have any combination of features not possessed by common stock, including properties of both an equity and a debt instrument, and is generally considered a hybrid instrument.", "takeaways": ["Terms of the preferred stock are described in the issuing company's articles of association or articles of incorporation.", "Like bonds, preferred stocks are rated by major credit rating agencies."], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preferred_stock"},
    {"id": "market-cap", "level": "入门", "category": "股票", "title": "Market capitalization——Market capitalization, sometimes referred to as market cap, …", "summary": "Market capitalization, sometimes referred to as market cap, is the total value of a publicly traded company's outstanding common shares owned by stockholders. Market capitalization is equal to the market price per common share multiplied by the number of common shares outstanding.", "takeaways": ["Market capitalization, sometimes referred to as market cap, is the total value of a publicly traded company's outstanding common shares owned by stockholders.", "Market capitalization is equal to the market price per common share multiplied by the number of common shares outstanding."], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Market_capitalization"},
    {"id": "shares-outstanding", "level": "入门", "category": "股票", "title": "Shares outstanding——Shares outstanding are all the shares of a corporation that …", "summary": "Shares outstanding are all the shares of a corporation that have been authorized, issued and purchased by investors and are held by them. They are distinguished from treasury shares, which are shares held by the corporation itself, thus representing no exercisable rights.", "takeaways": ["Shares outstanding are all the shares of a corporation that have been authorized, issued and purchased by investors and are held by them.", "The basic count is the current number of shares.", "If the company has any diluting securities, this indicates the potential future increased number of shares outstanding."], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shares_outstanding"},
