    {"id": "dividend-basics", "level": "入门", "category": "股票", "title": "Dividend——A dividend is the distribution of profits by a corporation t…", "summary": "A dividend is the distribution of profits by a corporation to its shareholders. When a corporation earns a profit or surplus, it is able to pay a portion of the profit as a dividend to shareholders. Any amount not distributed is taken to be re-invested in the business (called retained earnings).", "takeaways": ["A dividend is the distribution of profits by a corporation to its shareholders.", "A dividend is allocated as a fixed amount per share, with shareholders receiving a dividend in proportion to their shareholding.", "The word dividend comes from the Latin word dividendum (\"thing to be divided\")."], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dividend"},
