    {"id": "share-repurchase", "level": "进阶", "category": "股票", "title": "Share repurchase——Share repurchase, also known as share buyback or stock buyba…", "summary": "Share repurchase, also known as share buyback or stock buyback, is the reacquisition by a company of its own shares. It is an alternative way of returning money to shareholders than dividends.", "takeaways": ["Share repurchase, also known as share buyback or stock buyback, is the reacquisition by a company of its own shares.", "More than 95% of the buyback programs worldwide are through an open-market method, whereby the company announces the buyback program and then repurcha…", "Rule 10b-18 provides a voluntary \"safe harbor\" from liability for market manipulation under Sections 9(a)(2) and 10(b) of the Securities Exchange Act …"], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Share_repurchase"},
    {"id": "secondary-offering", "level": "进阶", "category": "股票", "title": "Secondary market offering——A secondary market offering, according to the U.S. Financial…", "summary": "A secondary market offering, according to the U.S. Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), is a registered offering of a large block of a security that has been previously issued to the public.", "takeaways": ["A secondary market offering, according to the U.S.", "The proceeds from the sale of the securities do not benefit the issuing company in any way.", "\"Secondary offering\" as described in this article is an offering on the secondary market which is non-dilutive, and is thus not a follow-on offering."], "marketLinks": ["SPY", "AAPL", "MSFT"], "sourceName": "Wikipedia / CC BY-SA 4.0", "sourceUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secondary_market_offering"},
